{
  "texts": [
    "Classification head: A temporal max-pool over T to produce a d-dimensional vector, followed by a linear layer R d → R K and softmax to yield class probabilities.We evaluate on the JapaneseVowels benchmark [8], which comprises LPCderived 12-dimensional frames from nine speakers pronouncing Japanese vowels.",
    "To ensure uniform input shape, all sequences are truncated or zero-padded to T = 25 frames.",
    "The dataset splits into 270 training and 370 test samples across Y = 9 classes.",
    "Table 1 summarizes its key statistics.",
    "We train f θ for 100 epochs using cross-entropy loss, with a batch size of 4."
  ]
}